title: For Sale/Trade:  Mossberg 535
postcontent: "What the hell is a Mossberg 535?!" you might ask, well somebody somewhere might have an answer. I'm somebody, I'm somewhere, and to answer that question its the venerable Mossberg 500 chambered to accept 3.5" shells. A little about this badboy: 28" barrel so you can eliminate the threat from a distance. How far? SO many yards. More yards than an 18" barrel. This beast has taken literally POUNDS of dove. I've never had the pleasure of using this glorious thunderstick against a gobbler, but I did get to use it to scare a jive turkey out of my garage.A little about this bad boy: - HiViz orange fiber optic front with brass bead rear for tactical fowl acquisition and elimination - Nickel bolt slide and brass trigger so you can look good while providing for your family - Elastic shotshell saddle because frugal and practical go hand in hand - Much like that freaky girlfriend you had in college(the kind of ugly one you didn't tell anyone about), you can choke it and squeeze a hot load through a tight holeIts as clean as a truck gun can be. No major dents/dings/scratches, and bluing is in good shape. Mossberg went all out and outfitted it with the least flashy walnut available. Its a Mossberg thru and thru so its kind of finnicky with ammo, particularly Winchester black box(I've fed her a diet of Fiocchi and she loves it). I'm open to all manner of trades, I also happen to like money.
